      <akn:section eId="sec_38_752_03">
        <akn:num>38-752.03</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Post-secondary preparation plan.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_38-752_03_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p></akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_38-752_03_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The Mayor shall issue a report that details the number of students that attend a post-secondary institution, including the number of students who attend each type, including:</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_38-752_03_c">
      <akn:num>(c)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Beginning with the graduating class of 2014, the Mayor shall require that each student attending public high school takes the SAT or the American College Testing program before graduation.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_38-752_03_d">
      <akn:num>(d)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The Mayor may exempt a student from the requirements of subsections (a)(1) and (c) of this section, if the Mayor determines that it would constitute an undue hardship on the student.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
